        </dl>

        <!-- Advanced — per-tier priority overrides. Hidden by default; first
             expand triggers a swal warning that must be acknowledged before
             the inputs unlock. See docs/specs/PER_TIER_PRIORITY_OVERRIDE.md. -->
        <details class="zram-advanced" id="zram-advanced-priorities">
            <summary><i class="fa fa-flask"></i> Advanced &mdash; override tier priorities</summary>
            <div class="zram-advanced-body">
                <div class="zram-advanced-warning">
                    <strong>Read this first.</strong> Tier ordering depends on these values.
                    ZRAM (Tier 1) must stay <em>strictly higher</em> than Disk (Tier 2) — if you invert
